div.p:
During the design phase, a benchmark was carried out to assess the main functions and sections of the H2IOSC MarketPlace front-end, with the aim of following accessibility guidelines and best practices not only in the digital humanities sector, but also taking into account the leaders in the technology and communications market. The H2IOSC MarketPlace, like its counterparts in Europe (Marras et al. 2025
                    ) has been designed to offer functionality on different levels to meet the needs of both administrators and users and catalogues services and resources; moreover, the main advancement being the ability to “orchestrate” multiple resources in a single application workflow (
                    Kondam 2024).
